dt-option.default:
        The default value for the `-init searchPanes.countWidth` paramater is `50px`. When this default value is in place the width of the count columns in the panes is 50 pixels.


        As standard, SearchPanes will set the width of the count column to 50 pixels.

        By overwriting this value in the initialisation, the count column will have a width of whatever is set. 

		The `-init searchPanes.countWidth` functionality is useful when custom messages have been declared when using `-init searchPanes.viewTotal`, `-init language.searchPanes.count` and `-init language.searchPanes.countFiltered` as if the messages are long then the display of the searchPane may become a bit cluttered. 





$(document).ready(function() {
    $('#example').DataTable( {
        searchPanes:{
            countWidth: '100px',
        }
    });
});



-init searchPanes.viewTotal
-init language.searchPanes.count
-init language.searchPanes.countFiltered
